# Day 036 - Google Ads Intro

## Introduction

Google Ads is one of the most powerful digital advertising platforms in the world. It allows businesses to promote products, services, websites, and brands through paid advertisements displayed across Google Search, YouTube, Gmail, and partner websites. Google Ads helps businesses reach targeted audiences quickly and generate traffic, leads, and conversions.

Unlike Search Engine Optimization (SEO), which focuses on organic traffic, Google Ads uses a paid advertising model where businesses pay to display ads to users searching for relevant keywords.

Google Ads is widely used in digital marketing because Google is the largest search engine globally. Millions of users search for products, services, and information every day, making Google Ads an effective platform for businesses to connect with potential customers.

In college marketing, educational institutions use Google Ads for:
- Admission campaigns
- Course promotions
- Placement branding
- Webinar registrations
- Student lead generation

Google Ads provides measurable results, audience targeting, and scalable advertising opportunities.

---

# Definition of Google Ads

Google Ads can be defined as:

> “An online advertising platform developed by Google where businesses create paid advertisements to reach targeted audiences.”

It focuses on:
- Paid advertising
- Audience targeting
- Search visibility
- Lead generation
- Marketing performance

